Lady Calaera,

Since I was old enough I have been your humble follower, your servant.  I
have always endeavored to strike out at evil where ever I found it and in
whatever form it may choose to take.  I have strived to always speak the
truth be it through word or action, as the smallest hint of deception would
give root to evil.  I will admit though, to having trouble being kind to
others in the past during an occasion or two.  I have found that some that
are supposed to be beacons of light to be cowardly or greedy at times. 
These were people that I expected more from, examples of what is moral and
good.  I fear the warrior blood of the Ryarl runs quite hot at times and I
met these people with contempt when my disappointment got the better of me,
despite their poor actions.  I realize now this was a mistake and that even
as I let my temper get the better of me I give darkness an opportunity to
take hold on my heart.  

I feel I have overcome this shortfall and am ready to serve you fully, Lady
Calaera.  If you will have me, I wish to take on the mantle of
responsibility and hardship that your mark holds.  I feel I can hold the
light steadfast where it waivers.  
~
